Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: Process Objective: To make sure that IT services are delivered effectively and efficiently. This includes fulfilling user requests, resolving service failures, fixing problems, as well as carrying out routine operational tasks.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To make sure CIs and services are constantly monitored, and to filter and categorize Events in order to decide on appropriate actions.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To manage the lifecycle of all Incidents. The primary objective of Incident Management is to return the IT service to users as quickly as possible.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To grant authorized users the right to use a service, while preventing access to non-authorized users. The Access Management processes essentially execute policies defined in IT Security Management. Access Management is sometimes also referred to as Rights Management or Identity Management.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To manage the lifecycle of all Problems. The primary objectives of Problem Management are to prevent Incidents from happening, and to minimize the impact of incidents that cannot be prevented. Proactive Problem Management analyzes Incident Records, and uses data collected by other IT Service Management processes to identify trends or significant Problems.
Prop.Label: Description

Shape.Name: Sub Process.80
Shape.Text: Maintenance of Event Monitoring Mechanisms and Rules

Prop.Name: sys_RepositoryName
Prop.Value: Maintenance of Event Monitoring Mechanisms and Rules
Prop.Label: Repository Name

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To set up and maintain the mechanisms for generating meaningful Events and effective rules for their filtering and correlating.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To filter out Events which can be ignored, and to assign categories to Events indicating their significance.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To interpret the meaning of an Event and select a suitable response.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To check if Events have been handled appropriately and may be closed. This process also makes sure that Event logs are analyzed in order to identify trends or patterns which suggest corrective action must be taken.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To solve a Major Incident. Major Incidents cause serious interruptions of business activities and must be solved with greater urgency. The aim is the fast recovery of the service, where necessary by means of a workaround. If required, specialist support groups or third-party suppliers (3rd Level Support) are involved. If the correction of the root cause is not possible, a Problem Record is created and the error-correction transfered to Problem Management.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: The processing status of outstanding Incidents is to be continuously monitored, so that counter-measures may be introduced as soon as possible if service levels are likely to be breached.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To submit the Incident Record to a final quality control before it is closed. The aim is to make sure that the Incident is actually resolved and that all information required to describe the Incident's life-cycle is supplied in sufficient detail. In addition to this, findings from the resolution of the Incident are to be recorded for future use.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To inform users of service failures as soon as these are known to the Service Desk, so that users are in a position to adjust themselves to interruptions. Proactive user information also aims to reduce the number of inquiries by users.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To fulfill Service Requests, which in most cases are minor (standard) Changes (e.g. requests to change a password) or requests for information.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To constantly monitor outstanding Problems with regards to their processing status, so that where necessary corrective measures may be introduced.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To ensure that - after a successful Problem solution - the Problem Record contains a full historical description, and that related Known Error Records are updated.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To supply Incident-related information to the other Service Management processes, and to ensure that that improvement potentials are derived from past Incidents.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To record and prioritize the Problem with appropriate diligence, in order to facilitate a swift and effective resolution.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To ensure that the other Service Management processes as well as IT Management are informed of outstanding Problems, their processing-status and existing Workarounds.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To monitor and control the IT services and infrastructure. The process IT Operations Management executes day-to-day routine tasks related to the operation of infrastructure components and applications. This includes job scheduling, backup and restore activities, print and output management, and routine maintenance.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To manage the physical environment where the IT infrastructure is located. Facilities Management includes all aspects of managing the physical environment, for example power and cooling, building access management, and environmental monitoring.
Prop.Label: Description

Shape.Name: Sub Process.272
Shape.Text: Maintenance of Catalogue of User Roles and Access Profiles

Prop.Name: sys_RepositoryName
Prop.Value: Maintenance of Catalogue of User Roles and Access Profiles
Prop.Label: Repository Name

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To make sure that the catalogue of User Roles and User Access Profiles is still appropriate for the services offered to customers, and to prevent unwanted accumulation of access rights.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To process requests to add, change or revoke access rights, and to make sure that only authorized users are granted the right to use a service.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To identify the underlying root cause of a Problem and initiate the most appropriate and economical Problem solution. If possible, a temporary Workaround is supplied.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To review the resolution of a Problem in order to prevent recurrence and learn any lessons for the future. Furthermore it is to be verified whether the Problems marked as closed have actually been eliminated.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To provide and maintain the tools, processes, skills and rules for an effective and efficient handling of Incidents.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To record and prioritize the Incident with appropriate diligence, in order to facilitate a swift and effective resolution.
Prop.Label: Description

Shape.Name: Sub Process.344
Shape.Text: Immediate Incident Resolution by 1st Level Support

Prop.Name: sys_RepositoryName
Prop.Value: Immediate Incident Resolution by 1st Level Support
Prop.Label: Repository Name

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To solve an Incident (service interruption) within the agreed time schedule. The aim is the fast recovery of the IT service, where necessary with the aid of a Workaround. As soon as it becomes clear that 1st Level Support is not able to resolve the Incident itself or when target times for 1st level resolution are exceeded, the Incident is transferred to a suitable group within 2nd Level Support.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: To solve an Incident (service interruption) within the agreed time schedule. The aim is the fast recovery of the service, where necessary by means of a Workaround. If required, specialist support groups or third-party suppliers (3rd Level Support) are involved. If the correction of the root cause is not possible, a Problem Record is created and the error-correction transferred to Problem Management.
Prop.Label: Description
